      • extractTimestamp

        public long extractTimestamp(java.lang.Integer element,
                             long previousElementTimestamp)
        从接口复制的说明: TimestampAssigner
        Assigns a timestamp to an element, in milliseconds since the Epoch.

        The method is passed the previously assigned timestamp of the element. That previous timestamp may have been assigned from a previous assigner, by ingestion time. If the element did not carry a timestamp before, this value is Long.MIN_VALUE.

        指定者:
        extractTimestamp 在接口中 TimestampAssigner<java.lang.Integer>
        参数:
        element - The element that the timestamp is wil be assigned to.
        previousElementTimestamp - The previous internal timestamp of the element, or a negative value, if no timestamp has been assigned, yet.
        返回:
        The new timestamp.

      • checkAndGetNextWatermark

        public Watermark checkAndGetNextWatermark(java.lang.Integer lastElement,
                                          long extractedTimestamp)
        从接口复制的说明: AssignerWithPunctuatedWatermarks
        Asks this implementation if it wants to emit a watermark. This method is called right after the TimestampAssigner.extractTimestamp(Object, long) method.

        The returned watermark will be emitted only if it is non-null and its timestamp is larger than that of the previously emitted watermark (to preserve the contract of ascending watermarks). If a null value is returned, or the timestamp of the returned watermark is smaller than that of the last emitted one, then no new watermark will be generated.

        For an example how to use this method, see the documentation of this class.

        指定者:
        checkAndGetNextWatermark 在接口中 AssignerWithPunctuatedWatermarks<java.lang.Integer>
        返回:
        Null, if no watermark should be emitted, or the next watermark to emit.
